+# 0284-r9-r1 — Specialists/laboratories rule compatibility fix
+
+## Purpose
+
+The 0284-r9 implementation refreshed `doc/README_CURRENT.md` and advanced the
+cumulative Projects installation guide to `0284-r9`. Three pre-existing
+architecture rules still depended on stable historical markers:
+
+- the three named 0282 architecture views;
+- the correlated artifact paths and milestone names from 0281;
+- the safe-default guide baseline `0284-r1-r5`.
+
+The refresh removed the first two marker groups and one rule incorrectly froze
+the guide's current version at the baseline value. The runtime contract and the
+r9 verifier were not implicated.
+
+## Correction
+
+This patch:
+
+1. restores the historical markers in a dedicated compatibility index inside
+   the current roadmap;
+2. keeps the active roadmap at 0284-r9 and 0285;
+3. changes the safe-default rule to require a current version declaration and
+   the preserved `0284-r1-r5` history row instead of demanding that the guide
+   remain permanently at that old version;
+4. leaves `templates/github/projects-repository/INSTALLATION.md` unchanged at
+   version `0284-r9`.
+
+## Boundaries
+
+```text
+runtime_modified: false
+scheduler_modified: false
+sql_modified: false
+qdrant_modified: false
+openvino_modified: false
+github_workflow_modified: false
+projects_installation_modified: false
+projects_installation_verified: true
+external_dependencies_added: false
+```
+
+The fix is documentation/rule compatibility only. It performs no backend,
+network, GitHub or ProjectV2 operation.
